**Summary of the Bug:**

**Test Scenario:**
1. Scrolled to the bottom of the editor where a paragraph block ("We have been working on this project more than three years...") was visible, but the block above it ("* * *" delimiter) was NOT visible (scrolled above the viewport).
2. Clicked the ⋮⋮ (six-dot drag icon) of the paragraph block to open the Block Tunes menu.
3. Selected "Move up" from the Block Tunes menu.

**Observed Result (Bug):**
- After clicking "Move Up", the page **jumped to the very top of the document** (showing the "Editor.js" heading, "Key features" section, etc.)
- The paragraph block that was moved is **no longer visible** in the viewport - it has been scrolled off screen.

**Expected Result:**
- After moving a block up, the moved block should remain visible in the viewport (or the viewport should scroll to keep the moved block visible).
- The page should NOT jump to the very top of the document.

This is a confirmed **scroll position bug** in the Editor.js "Move Up" block tune functionality. When a block is moved up and the target position is outside the current viewport, the page incorrectly jumps to the very top of the document instead of smoothly scrolling to keep the moved block in view.

